    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="506"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.573 Whale Oil/18</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-06">August 6,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Norwegian Minister called and very earnestly urged sustained interest in
                    support of the Tonry Bill in the House of Representatives to repeal the duty on
                    whale oil. I stated that Dr. Sayre, Dr. Grady, <pb facs="0701" n="625"
                        xml:id="pg_625"/> myself and others in the Department had steadily brought
                    every possible influence to bear in support of this measure; that we were of
                    course extremely anxious for its enactment. I added that I would closely check
                    on the situation to date and take any further steps not already taken to
                    facilitate the passage of the measure. The Minister then stated that Congressman
                    Samuel Hill, Chairman of the sub-Committee of the Ways and Means Committee which
                    has this bill in charge, was reported on yesterday to have said that there was
                    enough sentiment probably to pass the bill through the Committee if somebody
                    would bring up the matter and emphasize and urge such action. I stated I would
                    be more than glad to do anything possible in this line without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
